-- Heat Beat Celtics in Overtime to Lead NBA Playoff Series 2-0
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-05-31T03:45:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/heat-beat-celtics-in-overtime-to-lead-nba-playoff-series-2-0.html
The  Miami Heat  beat the Boston
Celtics 115-111 in overtime to lead their National Basketball
Association playoff series by two games to none.  The winner of the best-of-seven Eastern Conference finals
will face the  San Antonio Spurs  or the Oklahoma City Thunder in
the NBA Finals. The Western Conference finals resume tomorrow in
Oklahoma City, with the home team trailing 2-0 in the series.  After two games in Miami, the Heat travel to Boston for
Games 3 and 4 on June 1 and 3.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  